      • onProgressUpdate

        public void onProgressUpdate(Request request,
                    java.lang.String placeholder)
        Method called the AbstractRequester while a request is made. The placeholder indicates the status of the request:
        • "A" => The request was successfully converted into JSON
        • "B" => Did you follow the connection with the server
        • "C" => You have received a response from the server
        • "D" => The response has been accessed
        • "E" => The response was converted from JSON to the type of class in the method send()
        Parameters:
        request - Reference to the instance of the Request
        placeholder - Indicates the status of the request Request.Status
        See Also:
        AsyncTask
